hopobject.body: A pension scheme huawei fit watch faces Not only was the film a pleasure to watch, but so too was the process by which it came together, as described by Amy Acker, who plays Beatrice."One of my favorite parts of the movie is that watching it feels the way it felt making it," she says of the film's raucous party sequence. Whedon, who provided his Santa Monica house for the shoot, invited his own friends – many of them alumni of his other works – to serve as extras. "They were the ones drinking, so the party moved to the front of the house and you had filming happening in the back. It was all really fun," Acker says.
